Subject: RE: CLAIM C90306048 -Fire at 23 Mays Street Devonport 2026-001966 =
[WYNNW-ACTIVE.FID3167762]

Hello Richard, and All,
Thanks for the reply sent to Tower Insurance below, received on April 9.
I have spoken with my colleagues, and we agree that Tower Insurance should =
provide further detailed response to each of the concerns presented within =
the Prendos Report. As such instructions have been issued as follows:


  1.  I have instructed ASURNZ to provide detailed response with respect to=
 the application of Schedule 1, and provide specific reference to the relev=
ant clauses within the Building Act 2004; and any other relevant legislatio=
n which will assist with determination on this issue. I will be able to pro=
vide that response to you by 4pm on Tuesday April 21.
  2.  I have instructed ASURNZ to appoint a CPEng to undertake an assessmen=
t of the unreinforced masonry walls to the perimeter of the basement level =
of the dwelling to ascertain if they have been materially affected by the l=
oss-event [fire].
  3.  I have instructed ASURNZ to appoint a CPEng to undertake an assessmen=
t of the existing wall bracing elements which are referred to in the Prendo=
s report.
  4.  I have instructed ASURNZ to provide drawings of construction details,=
 specification references, and other documents which will assist with authe=
nticating the aspects of the repairs which are currently within the propose=
d scope of works. This should provide further clarity and detail for all pa=
rties to review.
  5.  I have instructed ASURNZ to include the replacement of existing therm=
al insulation to the external basement walls into the proposed scope of wor=
k.

To complete all the above we request permission to access the property at 9=
am on Thursday April 16 to allow for assessments and observations to be com=
pleted. Noting that item #4 may take a while longer to provide as the drawi=
ngs will be produced from additional notes & observations taken on the prop=
osed site visit.

Persons who would be present at this site review are as follows:


  1.  Grant Metson =E2=80=93 Regional Manager, Structural Assessing, Tower =
Insurance.
  2.  Warwick Banks =E2=80=93 CPEng. KCL Engineering.
  3.  Stephen Walker =E2=80=93 Principal Consultant, ASURNZ.

Please relay this request to Raffaella Del Prete, in order that we receive =
her permission to visit the property to complete the above, at the date and=
 time prescribed.
Please confirm at your earliest ability, so I can reconfirm this with all p=
arties.
Best Regards,
Grant.

